The paper deals with output coding for multi-label prediction, which is a problem commonly encountered in machine learning and pattern recognition. The paper proposes a max-margin formulation for finding output codes that are both discriminative and predictable, which is a common approach in the field of machine learning. The empirical study focuses on image, text, and music classification, which are all areas of research that fall under the umbrella of computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
